    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a high-variance slate today, with **Yordan Alvarez** (82.00) leading the charge. His elite xwOBA of 0.393 combined with a significant 16% park factor boost makes him our clear daily anchor against Baz. Just behind him, the speed factor is in full effect: **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.78) is our most aggressive start, as he faces a Walker Buehler matchup that offers both a 19% SP skill advantage and a slow delivery profile that drastically increases his stolen base upside. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (76.32) and **Kyle Schwarber** (73.95) are both strong plays against Mahle, with **Trea Turner** benefitting from his leadoff spot and **Kyle Schwarber** capitalizing on his elite 0.402 xwOBA to maximize run production.\n\nTactically, we are leaning into platoon advantages to squeeze out value, specifically with **Dillon Dingler** (63.90), whose dynamic platoon edge against P\u00e9rez provides a substantial 14% lift, making him our preferred catcher despite the uncertain floor. **Junior Caminero** (70.81) also continues to demonstrate why he belongs in the UTIL slot, as his high base projection is further elevated by a favorable top-of-the-order opportunity. **Chase Meidroth** (41.63) was the hardest exclusion from today's lineup; he remains a viable depth piece, but the combination of a neutral platoon matchup and a negative adjustment for his assumed #7 order slot kept him just below our threshold for active consideration. \n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" statuses of **Gary Sanchez**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Pete Crow-Armstrong**. While their projections remain high based on historical placement, any significant shift down the order could necessitate a pivot to protect our daily game caps. Furthermore, while **Luke Raley** offers a slight stolen base opportunity, his matchup against Ryan is the most dangerous of the day given the 3.32 xERA; we are starting him for his sprint speed, but his 45.66 score suggests he is on the lower end of our active tier and should be monitored closely. With **Christian Yelich** and **Colt Keith** still unavailable, our depth will be tested if any of these late-order threats fail to clear the baseline.",
